Well as I just mentioned,

00:01:18.960 --> 00:01:22.410
this bank is already at
its minimum reserves.

00:01:22.410 --> 00:01:25.220
It's already loaned out
as much as it could.

00:01:25.220 --> 00:01:29.120
If you get $2,000 in deposits
and you have a 10% reserve

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:32.330
ratio, that means you can
loan out 90% of that $2,000

00:01:32.330 --> 00:01:35.604
and it has already loaned
out 90% of the $2,000.

00:01:35.604 --> 00:01:38.420
So what is the dollar value of new loans

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:40.290
