00:02:14.890 --> 00:02:17.190
Well there's a couple of ways
you could think about it.

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:20.080
Before Mr. Smith makes
that deposit we already saw

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:23.229
in part A that First Superior
Bank can't make any new loans

00:02:23.229 --> 00:02:27.743
and so now if it gets $100
of cash in a demand deposit

00:02:27.743 --> 00:02:30.379
account because the reserve ratio is 10%,

00:02:30.379 --> 00:02:33.811
the bank needs to keep 10%
of that deposit as reserves

00:02:33.811 --> 00:02:37.080
and it can loan out the other 90%.

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:40.250
So you could just say well it
could loan out 90% of that new

00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:44.737
deposit and so it would be 90% times $100

00:02:45.998 --> 00:02:50.998
