00:02:51.105 --> 00:02:53.370
Another way that you
could think about it is

00:02:53.370 --> 00:02:57.040
after Mr. Smith's deposit,
the demand deposits right over

00:02:57.040 --> 00:03:01.790
here goes to $2,100 and
that increase in liabilities

00:03:01.790 --> 00:03:03.510
is offset by an increase in assets.

00:03:03.510 --> 00:03:06.460
It just got $100 of cash so the reserves

00:03:06.460 --> 00:03:09.998
go from $200 to $300.

00:03:09.998 --> 00:03:13.939
Now at this point, First
Superior Bank is clearly above

00:03:13.939 --> 00:03:16.660
its minimum reserve requirements.

00:03:16.660 --> 00:03:20.740
300 over 2,100 is more than 10%.

00:03:20.740 --> 00:03:22.760
So it can loan out some money.

00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:24.270
How much could it loan out?

00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:27.878
Well it has to keep 10%
of this $2,100 as reserves

00:03:27.878 --> 00:03:32.740
so it needs to keep $210 right over here

00:03:32.740 --> 00:03:35.480
and so that other $90 it could loan out.

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:36.830
And so this could be $1,890

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:42.193
and so it can make $90 in new loans.

