Well as we just said Mr.
Smith by depositing $100.

00:04:06.529 --> 00:04:10.155
First Superior Bank can make $90 of loans

00:04:10.155 --> 00:04:12.842
so that would be $90 of
new loans but then whoever

00:04:12.842 --> 00:04:15.850
they loan that money to,
they could then deposit

00:04:15.850 --> 00:04:18.960
that in a bank and then
that bank could loan out

00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:23.960
90% of that, so then it
would be plus 0.9 times 90.

00:04:25.130 --> 00:04:30.130
Now this bank that got 0.9
times $90 which is $81,

00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:33.390
it can then loan out 90% of that.

00:04:33.390 --> 00:04:37.203
So it's gonna be plus 0.9 times this,

00:04:37.203 --> 00:04:40.657
so 0.9 squared times 90
and you just keep going

00:04:40.657 --> 00:04:42.845
like this and then this
gives us essentially

00:04:42.845 --> 00:04:45.100
the equation for the multiplier

00:04:45.100 --> 00:04:46.670
which you might have memorized.

00:04:46.670 --> 00:04:47.740
This is just going to be equal

00:04:47.740 --> 00:04:52.740
to 90 times one over one
minus you could say this 0.9

00:04:56.215 --> 00:04:58.208
or you could say this is the same thing as

00:04:58.208 --> 00:05:03.130
90 times one over the
reserve ratio which is 0.1

00:05:03.130 --> 00:05:06.990
and one over .1 is 10 so this
is going to be equal to $900.

